shape: sequence_diagram

# Participants
User: Human Player
Frontend: Web Frontend (TypeScript)
Backend: Web Application (TS)
Engine: Rust Module (Engine)
DB: Database

# Scenario: Human Player makes a move
User -> Frontend: Selects cell on board
Frontend -> Backend: Send move request (position)
Backend -> DB: Retrieve current match state
DB -> Backend: Return match data

# Internal Validation & Engine Call
# TODO: replace this for the actual call
Backend -> Engine: POST /verify (Move + State in YEN notation)
Engine -> Engine: Check move validity
Engine -> Engine: Verify win/loss status
Engine -> Backend: Return verification result (JSON)

# Finalizing the Turn
Backend -> DB: Persist updated match state
DB -> Backend: Confirmation
Backend -> Frontend: Updated board state (YEN notation)
Frontend -> User: Render new board & show status